</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E84FF0A48F757CCFB1FFF07" box="[199,1210,223,248]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="007606418E84FF0A48F757CCFB1FFF07" blockId="202.[151,1437,151,2022]" box="[199,1210,223,248]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">
World species. One hundred and fifty four species are known, nine in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E84FF0A4C3857F3FB10FF07" box="[1032,1205,223,247]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E84FF0A48F75628FB13FEEC" box="[199,1206,260,284]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418E84FF0A48F75628FB13FEEC" blockId="202.[151,1437,151,2022]" box="[199,1206,260,284]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">
Remarks. Fossil species of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E84FF0A4A325628FD3EFEEC" authorityName="R. Perkins" authorityYear="1907" box="[514,667,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Deinodryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E84FF0A4A325628FD3EFEEC" box="[514,667,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">Deinodryinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described by Guglielmino &amp; Olmi (2011).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E84FF0A48A75643FA39FB7F" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" type="key">
